{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.eigenfunction_completeness\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">OneDimension</span>.<span class=\"name\">HarmonicOscillator</span>.<span class=\"name\">eigenfunction_completeness</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator\">HarmonicOscillator</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">plancherel_theorem</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∀ {<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>},\n    <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/L1Space/Integrable.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable\">MeasureTheory.Integrable</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n      <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.MemLp\">MeasureTheory.MemLp</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Fourier/Notation.html#FourierTransform.fourier\">FourierTransform.fourier</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>           <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Span/Defs.html#Submodule.span\">Submodule.span</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.range\">Set.range</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span></span></span>)</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/Basic.html#Submodule.topologicalClosure\">topologicalClosure</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Assuming Plancherel's theorem (which is not yet in Mathlib),\nthe topological closure of the span of the eigenfunctions of the harmonic oscillator\nis the whole Hilbert space.\n\nThe proof of this result relies on `fourierIntegral_zero_of_mem_orthogonal`\nand Plancherel's theorem which together give us that the norm of\n\n`f x * e ^ (- x^2 / (2 * ξ^2))`\n\nis zero for `f` orthogonal to all eigenfunctions, and hence the norm of `f` is zero.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.eigenfunction_completeness","kind":"theorem","line":501,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.eigenfunction_completeness","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L501-L532"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_eigenVector\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">OneDimension</span>.<span class=\"name\">HarmonicOscillator</span>.<span class=\"name\">zero_of_orthogonal_eigenVector</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator\">HarmonicOscillator</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↥<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace\">HilbertSpace</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hOrth</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">plancherel_theorem</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∀ {<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>},\n    <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/L1Space/Integrable.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable\">MeasureTheory.Integrable</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n      <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.MemLp\">MeasureTheory.MemLp</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Fourier/Notation.html#FourierTransform.fourier\">FourierTransform.fourier</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>           <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_eigenVector","kind":"theorem","line":494,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_eigenVector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L494-L499"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_mk\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">OneDimension</span>.<span class=\"name\">HarmonicOscillator</span>.<span class=\"name\">zero_of_orthogonal_mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator\">HarmonicOscillator</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.MemHS\">HilbertSpace.MemHS</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hOrth</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">hf</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">plancherel_theorem</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∀ {<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>},\n    <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/L1Space/Integrable.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable\">MeasureTheory.Integrable</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n      <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.MemLp\">MeasureTheory.MemLp</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Fourier/Notation.html#FourierTransform.fourier\">FourierTransform.fourier</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>           <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSeminorm/Defs.html#MeasureTheory.eLpNorm\">MeasureTheory.eLpNorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">hf</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_mk","kind":"theorem","line":447,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.zero_of_orthogonal_mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L447-L492"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.fourierIntegral_zero_of_mem_orthogonal\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">OneDimension</span>.<span class=\"name\">HarmonicOscillator</span>.<span class=\"name\">fourierIntegral_zero_of_mem_orthogonal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator\">HarmonicOscillator</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.MemHS\">HilbertSpace.MemHS</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hOrth</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">hf</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Fourier/Notation.html#FourierTransform.fourier\">FourierTransform.fourier</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Real.exp\">Real.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> (<span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Q</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.ξ\">ξ</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)))</span></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` is a function `ℝ → ℂ` satisfying `MemHS f` such that it is orthogonal\nto all `eigenfunction n` then the fourier transform of\n\n`f (x) * e ^ (- x ^ 2 / (2 ξ^2))`\n\nis zero.\n\nThe proof of this result relies on `orthogonal_exp_of_mem_orthogonal`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.fourierIntegral_zero_of_mem_orthogonal","kind":"theorem","line":422,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.fourierIntegral_zero_of_mem_orthogonal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L422-L445"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.orthogonal_exp_of_mem_orthogonal\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"name\">OneDimension</span>.<span class=\"name\">HarmonicOscillator</span>.<span class=\"name\">orthogonal_exp_of_mem_orthogonal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator\">HarmonicOscillator</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.MemHS\">HilbertSpace.MemHS</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hOrth</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HilbertSpace/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HilbertSpace.mk\">HilbertSpace.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">hf</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Complex.exp\">Complex.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex.I\">Complex.I</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">c</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">x</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Real.exp\">Real.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> (<span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Q</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Basic.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.ξ\">ξ</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)))</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` is a function `ℝ → ℂ` satisfying `MemHS f` such that it is orthogonal\nto all `eigenfunction n` then it is orthogonal to\n\n`e ^ (I c x) * e ^ (- x ^ 2 / (2 ξ^2))`\n\nfor any real `c`.\nThe proof of this result relies on the expansion of `e ^ (I c x)`\nin terms of `x^r/r!` and using `orthogonal_power_of_mem_orthogonal`\nalong with integrability conditions. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.orthogonal_exp_of_mem_orthogonal","kind":"theorem","line":255,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.orthogonal_exp_of_mem_orthogonal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L255-L417"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Completeness.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.orthogonal_power_of_mem_orthogonal\"><span class=\"name\">QuantumMechanics</span>.<span class=\"